t xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"translate(145.91098557692305 291.84) rotate(-40)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">male</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"195.27884615384613\" y=\"127.55555555555557\" height=\"144.44444444444443\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#666666\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"218.99399038461536\" y=\"249.77777777777777\" height=\"22.22222222222222\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#CCCCCC\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"242.70913461538458\" y=\"260.8888888888889\" height=\"11.11111111111111\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#000000\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"translate(240.77156249999996 291.84) rotate(-40)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">female</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"290.13942307692304\" y=\"272\" height=\"0\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#666666\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"313.85456730769226\" y=\"238.66666666666669\" height=\"33.33333333333333\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#CCCCCC\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"337.5697115384615\" y=\"105.33333333333334\" height=\"166.66666666666666\" width=\"23.71514423076923\" fill=\"#000000\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"translate(335.63213942307686 291.84) rotate(-40)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">undetermined</text><text text-anchor=\"middle\" transform=\"translate(230.8515625 24)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Banded Sand Catsharks Found in </text><text text-anchor=\"middle\" transform=\"translate(230.8515625 48)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Three Sponges</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" fill=\"none\" x=\"153.203125\" y=\"413.682373046875\" height=\"103\" width=\"108.59375\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"160.203125\" y=\"425.682373046875\" height=\"12\" width=\"12\" fill=\"#666666\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text transform=\"translate(182.203125 437.682373046875)\" text-anchor=\"top\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\"> sponge 1</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"160.203125\" y=\"457.682373046875\" height=\"12\" width=\"12\" fill=\"#CCCCCC\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text transform=\"translate(182.203125 469.682373046875)\" text-anchor=\"top\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\"> sponge 2</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"160.203125\" y=\"489.682373046875\" height=\"12\" width=\"12\" fill=\"#000000\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text transform=\"translate(182.203125 501.682373046875)\" text-anchor=\"top\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\"> sponge 3</text></g></svg></figure><div class=\"sr-only\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Long description for bar graph titled Banded Sand Catsharks Found in Three Sponges\"><ul>\n<li>For each data category, the following bars are shown:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>sponge 1</li>\n<li>sponge 2</li>\n<li>sponge 3</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Number of sharks data for the 3 categories are as follows:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>male:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>sponge 1: 17 sharks</li>\n<li>sponge 2: 1 shark</li>\n<li>sponge 3: 2 sharks</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>female:&nbsp;<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>sponge 1: 13 sharks</li>\n<li>sponge 2: 2 sharks</li>\n<li>sponge 3: 1 shark</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>undetermined:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>sponge 1: 0 sharks</li>\n<li>sponge 2: 3 sharks</li>\n<li>sponge 3: 15 sharks</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div>\n<p>Researcher Helen O&rsquo;Neill and her team were studying sponges in the family Irciniidae when they discovered that three of the sponges were functioning as microhabitats for banded sand catsharks (<em>Atelomycterus fasciatus</em>). Additionally, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Referenced Content\">the team found that male and female <em><span data-ssml-sub-alias=\"A\">A.</span> fasciatus</em> share the same sponge (the same microhabitat)</span>, a behavior not found among Port Jackson sharks (<em>Heterodontus portusjacksoni</em>), another seabed-dwelling species.</p>"
}